# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# .gitignore audit notes (SPO-33, SPO-34)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Historical footgun: a bare directory pattern (no leading `/`) matches that
# directory name RECURSIVELY at any depth. In a monorepo this can silently
# hide real source code — e.g. `models/` used to shadow
# `packages/ml-in-sports/src/ml_in_sports/models/` (Kelly math, dataclasses).
#
# Rules of thumb when adding entries:
#   1. Prefer a leading `/` when the pattern should only match at repo root
#      (e.g. build outputs, data dumps, coverage, MLflow runs).
#   2. Keep recursive (no `/`) only for patterns that CANNOT legitimately be
#      source code anywhere — caches, `__pycache__`, IDE dirs, node_modules.
#   3. Every recursive directory pattern on a plain English word deserves a
#      one-line comment justifying why it's safe to recurse.
#   4. Never add `models/` — it was the bug. Trained model files are caught
#      by extension patterns (*.pkl, *.joblib, *.h5, *.pt, ...).

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Python — caches and compiled artifacts
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Recursive is safe here: these names cannot be legit Python source.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# Python build outputs — recursive on purpose: `uv build` / `hatch build`
# emit these per-package (packages/<pkg>/build/, packages/<pkg>/dist/).
# Narrowing to `/build/` would leak per-package build artifacts into git.
build/
dist/

# Setuptools legacy — narrowed to root-only. These names (`lib`, `parts`,
# `var`, `eggs`, `wheels`, `sdist`, `downloads`, `develop-eggs`) are plausible
# as Python submodule names inside packages/* and apps/*. uv + hatchling
# don't emit them at nested levels, so root-only is sufficient.
/develop-eggs/
/downloads/
/eggs/
/.eggs/
/lib/
/lib64/
/parts/
/sdist/
/var/
/wheels/
/share/python-wheels/

# Virtual environments
# Recursive on purpose: we never want a venv committed, and `.venv` / `venv`
# are not legitimate source identifiers. `env/` and `ENV/` narrowed to
# root-only because `env` is plausible as a submodule name (e.g. env config).
.venv/
venv/
/ENV/
/env/
.python-version

# uv
.uv/
uv.lock

# Poetry (legacy, usuwane w P1)
poetry.lock

# pytest
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
/htmlcov/
.hypothesis/
coverage.xml
*.cover
.tox/

# mypy
.mypy_cache/
.dmypy.json
dmypy.json

# ruff
.ruff_cache/

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb_checkpoints

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Node / TypeScript
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Recursive: these names cannot be legit source in a JS/TS workspace.
node_modules/
.next/
.turbo/
.cache/
*.tsbuildinfo
.pnpm-store/
.yarn/

# Env files
.env
/infra/.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.production
.env.development
.env.test

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Data & Models (never commit)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# `/data/` narrowed to root-only (SPO-34). A nested `packages/foo/data/`
# — e.g. seed fixtures, test data, team_name_replacements.json siblings —
# must stay trackable. Large datasets belong outside the repo anyway.
/data/
*.parquet
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.csv
*.xlsx

# Model artifacts
#
# NOTE: do NOT add `models/` here — there is a Python subpackage at
# packages/ml-in-sports/src/ml_in_sports/models/ containing source code
# (dataclasses, Kelly math). A bare `models/` pattern matches it recursively
# and makes it untrackable. Trained-model files are caught by the file-extension
# patterns below. See SPO-33.
#
# `/mlruns/` and `/mlflow/` narrowed to root-only (SPO-34): MLflow tracking
# is single-instance at repo root; nested `mlflow/` subdirs would be legit.
/mlruns/
/mlflow/
*.pkl
*.joblib
*.h5
*.onnx
*.pt
*.pth
*.safetensors

# Logs — narrowed to root-only (SPO-34). `logs/` is plausible as a submodule
# (e.g. a logging helper package) or a docs subdir. The `*.log` glob still
# catches stray log files at any depth.
/logs/
*.log

# Output / artifacts / reports — narrowed to root-only (SPO-34).
# HIGH COLLISION RISK if recursive:
#   - `reports/` would shadow `docs/reports/` (reporter agent output) and
#     any future `apps/api/reports/` route module.
#   - `artifacts/` would shadow CI artifact subdirs and any `packages/*/
#     artifacts/` fixture dir.
#   - `output/` would shadow ML pipeline output submodules.
# Keep root-only so ad-hoc scratch dirs at repo root remain ignored.
/output/
/artifacts/
/reports/
*tmp*
*temp*

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# IDE / Editor
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets (NEVER commit)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
*.pem
*.key
*.cert
*.crt
credentials.json
secrets.json
.secrets/
.doppler/

# MCP project-scope config (may contain tokens in headers)
.mcp.json
.mcp.local.json

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
.docker/

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# OS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
